data.value: Intorducing Thor, one of our few dogs that have made their way to the UK from the scroching desert climate of Qatar. Born in our shelter to a pure GSD mother, and whippet father. Little Thor was fostered or adopted nad has spent the last 2 years being overlokked in our shelter kennels. However the lovely lady in the UK who adopted her sister always asked after the one left behind, and wanted to make it up to her...The rest is history,we got her rabies serology done, she's waited the time, money was raised, and she is now awaiting a home and available in the UK! New name Thor, she is now ready for her family to come and meet her. She has settled in after travel, and house trained easily. She loves people, attention and lots of cuddles. Having came from a very busy shelter environment, she would be best suited as an only dog as she learns about family life.
